sp.p:
Is that my fault ? But you may pay too dearly even for a lady housekeeper—it's right you
     should know she's a confirmed mischief maker! So be on your guard against Mrs. Colonel Mac;
     and above all, don't believe in the character she is likely to give you of me.

On the contrary we must help ourselves, or be posted as defaulters, so make haste
     and drown your conscience for the day, Slack, it's a nuisance—and let me have the money;
     mind—my name mustn't appear in the affair.

Monee will take care. Oh! may Krishma bless the mem sahib for this ! Monee will creep
     through the compound like a snake. She'll be back before the shadows of the verandah pillars
     are there. (points, and exit rapidly).}

I've nae asked her. But ye ken my position, Mrs. Mac; I've earned my retiring pension ;
     I've saved half a lac to boot. I'm no jest a young man; but I've a constitution like bent
     leather; and as for my principles—
